-- 
4Kids Entertainment Inc. Files for Bankruptcy in New York

-- B y   D a w n   M c C a r t y
-- 
2011-04-06T18:51:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/4kids-entertainment-inc-files-for-bankruptcy-in-new-york-1-.html
4Kids Entertainment Inc. (KIDE) , a
children’s entertainment and merchandise licensing organization,
filed for bankruptcy.  The company and its affiliates had assets of $23.4 million
and debt of $16.5 million as of March 31, according to court
papers filed today in  U.S. Bankruptcy Court  in Manhattan.  Through its affiliates, 4Kids produces animated television
series and films. The company also programs and sells national
advertising time in “TheCW4Kids,” which airs nationally on The
CW Network on Saturday mornings. Prescott Group Capital
Management LLC owns 17.84 percent, court papers show.  The case is 4Kids Entertainment Inc., 11-11607, U.S.
Bankruptcy Court, District of New York (Manhattan).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dawn McCarty in Wilmington, Delaware, at 
 dmccarty@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
John Pickering at 
 jpickering@bloomberg.net  